examples.en: Jon disagreed, but did not feel disposed to argue.
He disposed of it without ceremony.
The next speaker quickly disposed of his weak argument.
She disposed of her parents' possessions
Mark was disposed to be wary after what had happened.
Chinese vases are disposed around the gallery.
Management is favourably disposed to the idea of job-sharing.
They are disposed to try soft means at first.
The experienced politician disposed of the attack in a few minutes.
Those children certainly disposed of all the food that I prepared for the party!
They disposed the surgical instruments in the exact order in which they would be needed.
